         I just don't see how parking your pet and going AFK in a lowbie spot for your level simply for faction purposes is a bannable offense or an exploit.  You aren't getting experience, simply faction.  If its bannable, then what is the point of being a high level.  If its bannable, then why even put factions into the game that can be altered for quest purposes and so forth.  If that is bannable, then is it bannable to park yourself in a small water area swimming into a corner to get up your swimming skill?  No.  Its just like that.  You are practicing swimming and here you are altering faction.  I have seen Ogres and DEs park there pets at the Goblin camps in Misty while they sit on the zone wall getting faction with Rivervale.  I don't see how that is bannable.  Its a way to alter faction that requires you to do exactly what any other person in the game must do to get the faction....kill stuff.  Its not like you are doing something that others cannot, or you are doing something that takes advantage of game mechanics.</P><P>   If they ban that then they might as well say "Hey, we are punishing you for being high level."  After all, isn't part of your reward for spending months on end getting to your level the ability to walk around lowbie zones if you want with impunity.  Are we not now powerful?</P><P>53rd Heretic of Misty Knight (Tholluxe Paels)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
